From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kyle Camera Local Quirk <kyle@example.invalid>
Subject: [PATCH] media: ipu-bridge: mark Dell XPS 14 DA14260 OV08X40 as inverted

The Dell XPS 14 DA14260 with OVTI08F4/OV08X40 reports a sensor rotation
of 0 degrees in firmware, but the image is physically upside down. Add a
DMI quirk so ipu-bridge publishes a 180 degree rotation fwnode property
for this sensor.
---
 drivers/media/pci/intel/ipu-bridge.c | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/media/pci/intel/ipu-bridge.c b/drivers/media/pci/intel/ipu-bridge.c
index 3e61790d64a6..7268243df6cf 100644
--- a/drivers/media/pci/intel/ipu-bridge.c
+++ b/drivers/media/pci/intel/ipu-bridge.c
@@ -128,6 +128,13 @@ static const struct dmi_system_id upside_down_sensor_dmi_ids[] = {
 		},
 		.driver_data = "OVTI02C1",
 	},
+	{
+		.matches = {
+			DMI_EXACT_MATCH(DMI_SYS_VENDOR, "Dell Inc."),
+			DMI_EXACT_MATCH(DMI_PRODUCT_NAME, "XPS 14 DA14260"),
+		},
+		.driver_data = "OVTI08F4",
+	},
 	{
 		.matches = {
 			DMI_EXACT_MATCH(DMI_SYS_VENDOR, "Dell Inc."),
-- 
2.54.0
